South Dakota Investment Council Has $2,420,000 Position in Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica (ERJ)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 7th, 2017 // No Comments




South Dakota Investment Council maintained its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica (NYSE:ERJ) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 109,600 shares of the aerospace company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. South Dakota Investment Council’s holdings in Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica were worth $2,420,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other institutional investors also recently made changes to their positions in ERJ. PNC Financial Services Group Inc. increased its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica by 1.7% in the first quarter. PNC Financial Services Group Inc. now owns 9,067 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $199,000 after buying an additional 152 shares during the period.  Comerica Bank increased its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica by 1.6% in the first quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 12,358 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $236,000 after buying an additional 198 shares during the period.  World Asset Management Inc increased its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica by 1.9% in the first quarter. World Asset Management Inc now owns 11,527 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $255,000 after buying an additional 211 shares during the period.  Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Services Inc. increased its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica by 8.4% in the fourth quarter. Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Services Inc. now owns 7,327 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $142,000 after buying an additional 570 shares during the period.  Finally, Nordea Investment Management AB increased its position in shares of  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica by 3.1% in the first quarter. Nordea Investment Management AB now owns 69,485 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $1,534,000 after buying an additional 2,114 shares during the period. Institutional investors own  49.57% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica alerts:



Shares of Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica (NYSE ERJ) opened at 18.70 on Friday. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $19.34 and a 200 day moving average of $20.95. The firm has a market cap of $13.75 billion, a P/E ratio of 137.50 and a beta of 0.35. Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica has a 52 week low of $17.06 and a 52 week high of $24.95. 





Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica (NYSE:ERJ) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The aerospace company reported $0.13 EPS for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.17 by $0.04. Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica had a net margin of 1.76% and a return on equity of 9.15%. The firm had revenue of $1.03 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.01 billion.  Equities analysts forecast that  Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica will post $1.78 earnings per share for the current year. 
The company also recently disclosed a special dividend, which will be paid on Thursday, July 20th. Shareholders of record on Thursday, June 15th will be issued a $0.0489 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Tuesday, June 13th. Embraer-Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica’s dividend payout ratio  is 29.83%. 
